  </div>

  <div class="comment-content">
    <div class="author"><div class="picture">
  <a href="/users/lewy14" title="View user profile."><img src="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/pictures/picture-1327.png" alt="lewy14&#039;s picture" title="lewy14&#039;s picture"  /></a></div>
</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>Bitcoin cannot be "printed", but it can, in fact, be "mined".</p>
<p>Google "mine bitcoin fpga".</p>
<p>If you can convert bitcoin for enough dollars to cover the variable cost of mining the bitcoin i.e. the cost of electricity - you have an arbitrage, and you will make money.</p>
<p>Bitcoin isn't exactly "energy backed", but it is energy-linked.</p>
<p>Not saying this is good or bad - just saying that folks who convert substantial assets to bitcoin should be aware of all the things influencing the conversion rate.</p>

